I) To install pydpiper, both the current source and most stable release can be 
   downloaded from github.  Using the Downloads button, access the .tar.gz or .zip file.:
    https://github.com/mfriedel/pydpiper

II) The 'setuptools' package is required to run the installation:
    http://pypi.python.org/pypi/setuptools

III) Unzip and untar and change into the source directory (e.g. cd pydpiper).

IV) Run: python setup.py install

In the event of an install error, check the output log to ensure all prerequisite packages are installed.

The py.test package (http://doc.pytest.org/en/latest/) is not required, but is necessary to run any 
of the test scripts found in /tests.
